cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about learning representations for object detection, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using the relationship between a candidate window and the ground truth bounding box of an object as supervision for representation learning, which is a form of supervised learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses handling semantic and visual variation, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions using multiple contexts and rotations to capture relationships, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM).
